<p></p>

<p>The TUSK infrastructure is currently in use at several schools in the United States and internationally as described below. Many other installations are in the planning stages.</p>

<p>In the United States</p>

<ul>
<li>New York Medical College </li>
<li>Boston University School of Medicine </li>
<li>John A. Burns School of Medicine at the University of Hawaii</li>
</ul>
<p>In Africa</p>

<ul>
<li>Muhimbili University College of Health Sciences, Dar es Salaam, Tanzania </li>
<li>Kenya Education Network Trust (Kenya), a network of schools of higher education in Kenya serving the University of Nairobi and Kenya Methodist University </li>
<li>Institute of Public Health, Makerere University, Kampala, Uganda</li>
</ul>

<p>In India</p>

<ul>
<li>Christian Medical College,Vellore India</li>
</ul>

<p>
TUSK was developed using open source software with open source standards. Our vision is to create a consortium of schools interested in co-developing an infrastructure that meets the educational needs of health sciences schools. If your school is interested in  working with us see our <a href="http://tusk.tufts.edu/about/contact_us">contact us page</a> to either call or email TUSK.
</p>


